result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Jason M. Jensen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jason M. Jensen is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jason M. Jensen was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

15CF47, 15CM9, and 15CM50.  Defendant Jason M. Jensen in court, in custody. Attorney Lisa A McDougal in court for Defendant Jason M. Jensen.  Prosecuting Atty Amy Elizabeth Forehand appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Counsel inform the Court that the parties have reached an agreement for resolution of three cases.

Atty. M details the agreement being proposed to the Court:

15CF47 - def to plead to count 1/stalking and count 2/misd. bail jumping for 6 months jail on count 2 and diversion agreement on count 1.

15CM9 - def to plead to counts 1, 2, and 3 for withheld sentence with 2 years probation and conditions to include costs, da education class, aoda/follow through, no drink, no contact with AJ or her daughters.  Also, restitution to be payable to R Hospital or Crime Victims Comp (if they pick up the bill; it's been submitted to them) $6440.40.  There is also a restitution request of $148.74 for AJ.  Atty. M - counsel request payment of restitution be paid through probation with whatever's not paid during probation to be made a civil judgment.  AD asks that JOC indicate that AJ be paid before the Richland Hospital.  

Court conducts colloquy on prelim waiver in 15CF47.  Court orders bindover.

Def pleads no contest to counts 1 and 2 of 15CF47 and to counts 1, 2, and 3 of 15CM9.  Court's colloquy on pleas.

24 days credit

Counsel and Def address the Court.

Court follows plea agreement but imposes longer probation:

12 mo diversion agreement ordered for count 1 of 15CF47.  Count 2 - 6 months jail - straight sentence with 24 days credit, with good time and huber.

15CM9 - 1, 2, and 3 - 3 years probation with conditions that he attend, pay for, and succ. complete d.a. class (24 to 26 week); no contact with AJ or any member of her family; pay restitution to her first of $148.74; then to R Hospital or Crime Victim Comp $6440.40; no possess/consume alcohol; submit to aoda/follow through; obey rules of probation; attend, pay for and complete any counseling/programs recommended by agent.  Pay costs of action.  Court orders one set of costs.

15CF47 - bond converted to signature bond - 1k - standard conditions - to be in effect while on DPA.

Remaining counts and 15CM50 dismissed.

Court orders def to provide DNA sample at the jail.
Request from DA's office to move the June 24th 1:30 hearing to 3:30; no objection from the Defense

Final pretrial set for 9/18 at 2.  Interim status set for 6/24 at 1:30.  If case is not resolved at that time, joinder motion will be taken up.
